          <text>
                    <body>
                              <p>My dear Sisters,*</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I hope that these lines will<lb/> find you in good
                                        health. We are well<lb/> here and I hope that we may
                                        enjoy<lb/> many more years. I am engaged.<lb/>
                                        <del>?</del> And pretty<lb/> far from here.
                                                  <persName>Kahn</persName> from
                                                  <placeName>Münster</placeName><lb/> proposed this
                                        engagement. My bride<lb/> is also related to him. Her
                                        brother<lb/> is married to the widow
                                                  <persName>Lowenstein<lb/> Ahans</persName> (?),
                                        the man who fell from the<lb/> attic. His name
                                                  <sic>isthe</sic> same as his<lb/> father,
                                                  <persName>Jacob</persName>. The wife of
                                                  <persName>Mr. Mastbaum</persName><lb/> in
                                                  <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> is the sister
                                        of my<lb/> future sister-in-law. She has a<lb/> sister.
                                        Maybe you know her through<lb/>
                                        <persName>Simon</persName>. When you see her, tell her<lb/>
                                        that <persName>Werther</persName> send her his regards.<lb/>
                                        Let her see the engagement announcement.<lb/> It has not yet
                                        been settled when the<lb/> marriage will be. I wish you
                                        were<lb/> here. Let me hear from you as soon<lb/> as
                                        possible.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">I remain your loving brother,</p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">Lipman
                                        Elkus</persName>.</p>
                              <p>I have been in <placeName>Rheine</placeName> last week. T<lb/> They
                                        are all well satisfied.</p>
                              <p>*<persName>Sarah</persName>
                                        <persName>Zipporah Elkus</persName> visiting their uncle
                                                  <persName>Isaac Leeser</persName><lb/> in
                                                  <placeName>Phila.</placeName> **<persName
                                                  role="author">Lipman Elkus</persName> born about
                                                  <date>1835</date>. (See letter
                                                  <placeName>Phila.</placeName>
                                        <date>May 30, 42</date><lb/> of <persName>Isaac
                                                  Leeser</persName> to <persName>Zalma
                                                  Rehine</persName>)<lb/> The three
                                                  <persName>Elkus'</persName> are the children of
                                                  <persName>Leah Leeser</persName> (sister of
                                                  <persName>Isaac</persName>)</p>
                    </body>
